1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,920
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,680
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:10,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:10,680
<i>I already have</i>
<i>the full list of your spies.</i>

5
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:14,240
Duangnet's body is not in here.
Then where the hell is my daughter?

6
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,080
The Seven Legends New Genesis Project?

7
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:20,160
These rogue agents

8
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,440
<i>are your only hope.</i>

9
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,760
You want me to go to Pha Mok,
the last place your agents were killed?

10
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,920
- Hey! Ow!
- Hey!

11
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,640
Hey!

12
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:34,600
If you let them die or disappear,
no one will complain, no one will know.

13
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:37,320
<i>But you might regret it later.</i>

14
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:51,360
Hey!

15
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,160
Die now!

16
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,720
Huh?

17
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,200
Hey! Grenade!

18
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,320
- Grenade!
- Grenade!

19
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,520
Grenade!

20
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:26,360
Hey!

21
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,360
- Hey!
- Hey, go!

22
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:28,560
Go. Hurry.

23
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,080
Hey!

24
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,000
Hey!

25
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,360
Huh?

26
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,640
I ran out of ammo.

27
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,760
Then, three,

28
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:00,320
two, one.

29
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,320
You've messed us up bad.

30
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,240
You're gonna blow my head off?

31
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,480
Yeah.

32
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,360
Sarge.

33
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:30,360
Sarge?

34
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,440
You!

35
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,200
Ow, yeah, get him off.

36
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,360
You hurt my friend, huh?

37
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,600
- Whoa, whoa!
- Hey.

38
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:00,720
- He's dead.
- He's dead.

39
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,000
- Really?
- Yeah.

40
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,000
Let go of him then.

41
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,440
Oh, he's like a vegetable.

42
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,440
Boss, what's so urgent?

43
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,200
<i>Are you even doing your job?</i>

44
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,080
<i>Something happened right under your nose</i>

45
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,320
<i>and you still don't know?</i>

46
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:37,520
Why didn't anyone tell me?

47
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:55,440
Sorry, Boss. I just heard about it now.

48
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:58,240
I'll deal with this intel immediately.

49
00:06:58,840 --> 00:07:01,760
<i>Pha Mok is my mega-project.</i>

50
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,920
<i>I put you in charge</i>

51
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,360
<i>because I trust you most.</i>

52
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:07,520
Yes, Boss.

53
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,120
<i>Don't make me step in again,</i>

54
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:13,120
<i>like when you let the government spies in.</i>

55
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,600
<i>Because that means</i>

56
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,520
<i>my network doesn't need you.</i>

57
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,800
Yes, Boss.

58
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,920
I'll find out who they are.

59
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,240
How far was that area from Pha Mok?

60
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,920
Why did no one know?

61
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,360
ONCB?

62
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,760
Drugs and our men,
all were wiped out completely.

63
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:44,680
If it were ONCB,
they'd want results to report.

64
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:51,160
So who are they,
bold enough to erase everything?

65
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:56,480
Could they be spies,
the ones who investigated us before

66
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,280
and were taken out by Boss?

67
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,520
What do you think?

68
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,560
Boss already has their full agent list.

69
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:06,920
If they come back,
the moment they step into Pha Mok,

70
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,080
our facial-recognition system
would get them.

71
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,800
Find out who they are.

72
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,080
Yes, sir.

73
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,480
Thank you.

74
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,720
You never disappoint me.

75
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:42,720
I'll investigate on my end, too.

76
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:47,480
Understood.

77
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:21,760
Sarge.

78
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,160
How are those four?

79
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,560
Safe, Sarge. Just scrapes.
A little ointment and they'll be fine.

80
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,480
- Mm.
- Yeah.

81
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:34,040
If you hadn't come,
we'd be down to just us by now.

82
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:35,760
Thanks, Boss.

83
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,920
Thank you.

84
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,760
When did I agree to be your boss?

85
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:48,040
Are you still mad about us beating you up?

86
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,400
If you are,

87
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,000
here, you can beat Akki up.

88
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,480
Yeah, Sarge, beat me up…
Hey! You started it, didn't you?

89
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:57,000
What? You kicked him
full force right here.

90
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,440
You told me to start it.

91
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,440
- Hey!
- Oh.

92
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,600
Enough clowning.

93
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:05,680
All of you are useless,
failures, losers since school.

94
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,080
- You idiots!
- Huh?

95
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:08,680
Idiots?

96
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,880
Sarge, wait.

97
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:16,640
What data is that?

98
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:18,680
Well…

99
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,920
"Data scraps" is a better term.

100
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,320
These are images and videos

101
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,680
hidden in the old agent team's cars,

102
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,760
parked in different places

103
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:32,760
while gathering intel
on Phoenix in Pha Mok.

104
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:37,360
But I heard those files were destroyed

105
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:40,000
- when all the agents were killed, right?
- Yeah, Sarge.

106
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:42,240
That's why I call them scraps.

107
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:46,520
These files were uploaded to the cloud.

108
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,840
Even if deleted,

109
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,040
I can recover them with AI.

110
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,200
Hey.

111
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,840
Whoa.

112
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,400
Hey.

113
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:06,040
Wait, that's Ms. Duangnet,
Director Pantong's daughter.

114
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,320
But the old agent team was wiped out.

115
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:11,320
How could that be? The upload date

116
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,040
before they were deleted was one week

117
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,680
after the entire team was killed.

118
00:11:16,760 --> 00:11:20,720
And Duangnet was officially listed
as dead on the mission.

119
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:26,120
And the man beside her

120
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,200
is suspected to be part
of the Phoenix network.

121
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:32,760
So that means…

122
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,520
Ms. Duangnet is a mole.

123
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,720
I never imagined

124
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:50,360
your daughter could be this ruthless.

125
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:53,120
How could she let our agents die
right in front of her?

126
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,400
- People like that can't be spared. Evil!
- Enough.

127
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,600
My chest already feels crushed.

128
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,160
Even if she's my beloved daughter,

129
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:09,720
if she betrayed us
and killed her own, I won't spare her.

130
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:12,640
I'll drag her to prison myself.

131
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:16,200
But if we go to Pha Mok now,

132
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:18,480
Phoenix will know immediately

133
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:21,440
that the government
hasn't abandoned the purge.

134
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:22,880
Understand?

135
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,400
So you'll just let it be like this?

136
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,600
- Hey, hey.
- Hey.

137
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:38,280
- Hey, hey.
- Sarge.

138
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:40,440
- Sarge.
- Oh, wow.

139
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,600
Disguised like that,

140
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,480
you're going solo?

141
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,960
You're all trash.

142
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,000
If I don't help,
you'll all be dead within a week.

143
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,680
Don't tell me you're going after
Pantong's daughter alone.

144
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,560
I'll capture her,

145
00:12:56,640 --> 00:13:00,280
- squeeze the secrets out, make her talk.
- Wow.

146
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,320
- How about that?
- Yeah.

147
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,760
- Then the job's done.
- Wow.

148
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:09,360
Let us help, Sarge,
in case you can't handle it.

149
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,880
- Yeah, we'll help.
- Hey, hey.

150
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,440
- She's just this small.
- Huh?

151
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:15,000
Two pushes and she'll scream.

152
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,800
You guys should pack up and go home.

153
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:20,280
- You bunch of losers.
- Huh?

154
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:23,320
- Seriously, Sarge?
- Hey. Oh?

155
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,560
Are you serious?

156
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,640
You're really going alone?

157
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,440
You idiots.

158
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,240
Watch closely.

159
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,920
I'll show you how the old dogs do it.

160
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,520
- Hey, hey.
- Hey.

161
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,040
- Sarge.
- You won't make it alone.

162
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,360
- Hey.
- You weren't joking?

163
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,720
- He's really going…
- Hey.

164
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,560
What the hell?

165
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,560
- Still no updates?
- None at all.

166
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,760
There are no traces.

167
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,600
Who are they?

168
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,440
Do we have to search everyone in Pha Mok?

169
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:26,040
If we do that,

170
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:29,480
gamblers and investors will all bail.

171
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:34,840
Take it slow, everyone here is ours.

172
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:36,880
We'll find them.

173
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,960
Thanks for the ride .

174
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,040
Wait.

175
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:50,480
Boss wants you to carry this.

176
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,800
He's worried about your safety.

177
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,800
No need.

178
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:57,400
Orders are orders. Just keep it.

179
00:14:58,160 --> 00:15:00,040
He doesn't trust anyone easily.

180
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:07,680
Whoa.

181
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,960
Why are they all over the place?

182
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,840
Clues.

183
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,920
Perfect timing. They were having fun.

184
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,920
Hey, what the hell?

185
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:55,160
Hey, hey.

186
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,280
Hey, hey.

187
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,839
- Ow! You're strong.
- Enough.

188
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:17,319
Oh? You bitch!
Even if you're a woman, I won't spare you!

189
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:18,319
Hey!

190
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,760
Hey!

191
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:42,080
Whoa, knife too?

192
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:49,040
Using a knife? Hey, hey.

193
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:05,880
Knife and pillow? Everything at once?

194
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,800
You guys are really packing up?

195
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:23,960
Once Sarge finishes questioning
Director Pantong's daughter

196
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:27,760
and finds Phoenix's boss,
mission's over, right?

197
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:29,360
Why are we staying then?

198
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,880
But he's been gone a while.

199
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:33,800
Quiet like this,
maybe he got taken out already.

200
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,520
You think a small woman can handle him?

201
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,600
- Mm.
- Yeah.

202
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,520
But we can't be sure. Guys.

203
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,680
Check out her profile.

204
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,200
- What?
- Look.

205
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:53,040
She completed
the counter-terror training from ERT.

206
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:53,960
- Hey.
- Hey.

207
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:58,000
She has a Hostage Negotiation certificate

208
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:00,760
from ILEA, USA.

209
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:06,040
Former disguise instructor for female
intelligence agents.

210
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:10,560
Border Patrol.
Advanced camouflage training

211
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,960
with special air units.

212
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:15,960
- Whoa.
- Damn.

213
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,200
Whoa.

214
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,680
Because you're pretty

215
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:38,840
and you left your underwear everywhere,

216
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,160
I went easy on you.

217
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,120
Gun?

218
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:45,800
Who are you?

219
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:51,120
If you want answers, talk nicely.
Put the gun away.

220
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,280
Hey, what are you doing?

221
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:01,000
Hey, hey, hey, don't.

222
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:05,800
What? No! This isn't funny. Don't shoot!

223
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:08,520
What are you doing?

224
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,120
I searched you.

225
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:15,840
No ID.

226
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:20,240
No phone. No social footprint.

227
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:25,000
Good. No identity at all.

228
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,480
- You could die nameless.
- Hey, hey, no.

229
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,560
You vicious beauty!
You ruthless bitch! You mole! You…

230
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,080
Mole?

231
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,040
You're a government agent?

232
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,880
Colonel Pantong sent you?

233
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,960
Fine.

234
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,200
If you don't answer,

235
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,000
I don't care.

236
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,040
Whoa, third shot already.

237
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:59,080
The odds say it should hit. Don't shoot!

238
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:02,920
Oh, no, no! No!
Basil chicken! Basil chicken!

239
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,280
What are you joking about?

240
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:06,840
Are you trying to buy time? No way.

241
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,520
I never leave any traces.

242
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:13,320
I'm not buying time.
Basil chicken! Basil chicken!

243
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,640
No skin.

244
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,280
Basil minced pork.

245
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:18,640
No fat.

246
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:19,880
Fried egg.

247
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,360
Runny yolk.

248
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,600
Soup.

249
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,040
No garnish.

250
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:28,840
What would you like to order?

251
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,560
Basil chicken, no skin.

252
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:32,320
Basil minced pork, no fat.

253
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:36,160
Fried egg, runny yolk. Soup, no garnish.

254
00:21:37,080 --> 00:21:38,040
All right.

255
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:42,800
Whatever happens, I have your back.

256
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:45,960
If things turn deadly,

257
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:48,360
that's our code.

258
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:52,960
So Dad sent you? A new agent?

259
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,920
Yes.

260
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,240
He said…

261
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,440
if I can't handle you

262
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:05,400
and wanted to know whether you still
serve the country or became a mole…

263
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,600
A mole? Me?

264
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,720
- Is everything all set?
- Yes.

265
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,160
Phoenix has arrived.

266
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:37,320
Clear to enter. Confirming orders.

267
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,920
- Let's go!
- Go, go!

268
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,520
Soon I'll know

269
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,400
who you really are, Phoenix.

270
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:11,560
They killed my entire team!
You think I don't want revenge?

271
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,080
- Hey, don't shoot! I'm dead!
- Huh?

272
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:15,760
- Don't shoot! No!
- Huh?

273
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:18,160
- Enough! Enough!
- Ah! I'm dead! Ah…

274
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,520
Here.

275
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,360
Fake bullets. The cylinder's fake too.

276
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:28,200
What kind of agent can't tell?

277
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:30,240
It looks real.

278
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:35,240
I thought I made it
because I just made merit.

279
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,200
I'm allergic to duck down.

280
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:53,480
As we agreed, let's do it.

281
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:57,680
Let's risk it.
Whatever happens, happens. Okay?

282
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,920
- Okay.
- Okay.

283
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,600
Shouldn't we wait a little longer?

284
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,000
You want them to strike first?

285
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:06,800
By now, Sergeant Dab's probably been
interrogated and spilled everything.

286
00:24:06,880 --> 00:24:09,160
All right, let's do this. We need a plan.

287
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,760
- We need a leader.
- Yes.

288
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,440
- All right?
- Let's do it.

289
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:28,480
So this is the Seven Legends spy team?

290
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,600
Hey, you mole!

291
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,680
Put the guns down.

292
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,520
Think it through.

293
00:24:41,640 --> 00:24:43,240
Look. There are plenty of guns here.

294
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:44,840
I said put the guns down.

295
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:45,760
- Yeah.
- Mm.

296
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:48,000
You're not putting them down?
Put them down!

297
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,440
- You're talking about her?
- You guys. Look.

298
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,840
She's going for the groin.
Just do it. Please.

299
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,960
- I'll do it for your little boy.
- Thanks.

300
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:09,480
It wasn't easy for me to get close enough
for them to trust me, Dad.

301
00:25:09,560 --> 00:25:12,720
I don't want the plan to fail again
because of this unreliable team.

302
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:14,800
I won't approve that plan.

303
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:18,000
- Dad.
- <i>It's too risky.</i>

304
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:23,040
Right now, they're the only option
to keep this mission moving.

305
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:25,640
They can't even handle me alone.

306
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:28,520
- Will you send me instead, sir?
- Shut up.

307
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:33,120
This mission needs pros, not amateurs.

308
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:36,080
No matter what,
I won't let you do this alone.

309
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,000
Give them a chance.

310
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:42,880
Maybe this time,
we'll get the best team yet.

311
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,320
Understood.

312
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:53,640
Didn't Tiangmon find it suspicious
having you as his secretary?

313
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:56,000
Nothing comes without sacrifice.

314
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:59,560
I had to erase my entire identity

315
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:02,440
and created a new one.

316
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:06,160
Risked myself to get close to them.

317
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:10,320
We're downloading data on everyone
entering Pha Mokover the last three days.

318
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:13,640
How long will it take?

319
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:18,360
There are a lot of people.
And they must use fake identities.

320
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,560
We need deeper checks.
It'll be a bit longer.

321
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,080
One day.

322
00:26:27,280 --> 00:26:28,760
Find out

323
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:31,680
who messed with the boss's clients.

324
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:33,000
If you fail,

325
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:35,200
get ready to kick the bucket.

326
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:40,680
And if anyone looks suspicious,
shoot them.

327
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:43,600
Yes, sir.

328
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:47,160
Call everyone in. We've got a meeting.

329
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:57,280
Phoenix isn't small-time.
Pha Mok is an all-in investment.

330
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:01,640
They're laundering crime into legality.

331
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:04,360
Which means

332
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:07,720
everyone entering Pha Mok now

333
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,000
is locked into the screening system.

334
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:17,320
Akki, you're a hacker. Hack the system.

335
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:19,120
- Yeah.
- Hey.

336
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:22,520
It's not that easy.

337
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:27,160
That system
can only be hacked from the inside.

338
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:30,240
If someone who isn't an insider like me
changes the data,

339
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:32,320
within two days

340
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,400
they'll know exactly
who the seven of you are,

341
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,760
where you're from,
and even who your parents are.

342
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:41,080
Sarge, she's got a point, right?

343
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,440
Yeah. Hey.

344
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:45,840
Sarge, I think you should just give in.

345
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:49,640
Same-sex marriage's legal now.
No gender divide anymore.

346
00:27:49,720 --> 00:27:51,680
With intel this tight,

347
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,000
I'll give in once.

348
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,080
Then let's start my plan.

349
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:03,000
<i>Natee Suriyont,</i>
<i>publicly, a rich resort owner,</i>

350
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,000
<i>the most luxurious one in Pha Mok.</i>

351
00:28:05,800 --> 00:28:07,960
<i>Destination for the elites worldwide.</i>

352
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:09,920
<i>That's the front.</i>

353
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,040
Just a made-up public profile.

354
00:28:12,880 --> 00:28:14,400
Behind the scenes,

355
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,280
he runs a human-trafficking ring
through his resort,

356
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:20,000
using it as a secret auction house
for wealthy buyers worldwide.

357
00:28:20,080 --> 00:28:22,760
Many women have been lured
into becoming victims.

358
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:27,560
Some disappeared, others were killed.

359
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,720
<i>Beauty, a pretty influencer</i>

360
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:39,400
<i>with nearly a million followers</i>
<i>across all platforms…</i>

361
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:41,880
Ms. Beauty, this way please.

362
00:28:43,120 --> 00:28:46,560
<i>…serves as a mouthpiece,</i>
<i>creating a positive image for Pha Mok,</i>

363
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:49,520
and making Phoenix and all
its illegal networks look legitimate.

364
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:53,200
So elegant,
why choose to side with the devil?

365
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:57,920
PROFILE
NAME: PRAEWPAN BUTNAMPETCH

366
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,120
- Hey.
- Hm?

367
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:00,160
What is it, Sarge?

368
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:01,080
NORMAL JOB: BUSINESSWOMAN
SECRET JOB: MONEY LAUNDERING FOR PHOENIX

369
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:07,000
Oh, I was just wondering if this gang
handpick people by looks or what?

370
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:08,120
Everyone's gorgeous.

371
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,480
- Yeah, true. Right?
- They're pretty.

372
00:29:10,560 --> 00:29:11,400
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

373
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:15,840
Praewpan, a young businesswoman,
owner of a finance and insurance company,

374
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,640
<i>and head of the money-laundering network</i>

375
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:20,600
<i>for Phoenix and its illegal operations.</i>

376
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:23,280
<i>Don't underestimate her</i>
<i>just because she is a woman.</i>

377
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,600
Too bad you're here now.

378
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:30,880
Otherwise, I might fly to Hong Kong

379
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,960
to invite you for dim sum,

380
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,160
at that place we once…

381
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,760
We just tried it once.

382
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,040
When I realized it tasted terrible,

383
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:52,800
spitting it out would've been rude,
so I swallowed it.

384
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:55,320
I didn't want to be impolite.

385
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:57,240
That's enough.

386
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:03,600
I called you here to give orders,
not to watch you bicker.

387
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:15,560
Tiangmon, a retired soldier,

388
00:30:16,120 --> 00:30:18,320
head of the largest network.

389
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:22,200
Phoenix's right-hand man,
the most powerful figure in Pha Mok.

390
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:24,200
He oversees online gambling sites

391
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:27,640
and call center scam operations that
generate the most revenue for Phoenix.

392
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:31,040
So that's it. I got it.

393
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,800
I have a plan now.

394
00:30:35,080 --> 00:30:37,240
Simple. The plan is…

395
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:40,480
Shake them pillar by pillar.
Destroy each network one by one.

396
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:43,600
Cut off their arms and legs.

397
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,560
Force Phoenix to show itself.

398
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:48,680
And avenge the spy team they murdered.

399
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:52,720
- Damn.
- Wow, that's brilliant.

400
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:56,240
Do we live in the same house?
Why did you copy my homework exactly?

401
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,800
You understand the orders?

402
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,760
- Roger that.
- Roger that.

403
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:05,040
Roger that.
She copied my homework exactly.

404
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:17,480
The plan I explained,
do you understand it, Sarge?

405
00:31:18,320 --> 00:31:21,120
Your father didn't call
a deaf guy to work here, did he?

406
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:24,640
So this is your nature.
No wonder you led others to their deaths.

407
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:27,840
- Hey.
- If you want a redemption,

408
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,440
just lower your ego. That's all.

409
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,840
You know how to contact me securely now.

410
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:38,400
Report everything.
And don't act beyond orders.

411
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,480
Understood?

412
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,080
This mission

413
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:49,720
won't just be about taking down Phoenix.

414
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:54,440
I swear I'll make you call me "darling."

415
00:31:57,360 --> 00:31:58,600
- Darling.
- Darling.

416
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,560
Call me darling.

417
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:05,000
You sure, Sarge? I'm afraid
next time she'll dig a grave for you

418
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:07,480
and send you six feet under instead.

419
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,120
Which one of you wants to go first?

420
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:14,080
Huh? Go first for what, Sarge?

421
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:15,360
Go under my foot!

422
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,360
SERGEANT DAB

423
00:32:36,720 --> 00:32:39,640
The bubble tea order
for the upstairs staff is ready.

424
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:40,880
You can leave it here.

425
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:44,920
But if I don't deliver them soon,
the ice will melt. They won't taste good.

426
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,440
Uh, with no badge, you can't go upstairs.

427
00:32:51,680 --> 00:32:53,240
I didn't do anything wrong

428
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:54,880
and the customer's already complained.

429
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:56,800
If I get a one-star rating, I'll complain

430
00:32:56,880 --> 00:33:00,080
that the pretty staff was mean
and wouldn't let me go up.

431
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:03,840
<i>They're faster than I expected.</i>

432
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:07,160
<i>In a few hours, all of you will be found.</i>

433
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:13,560
<i>Shit.</i>

434
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:15,840
<i>Didn't you say you had it handled?</i>

435
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:18,240
<i>I just had the first team</i>
<i>start the mission.</i>

436
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:24,440
<i>It's fine, Sarge.</i>
<i>The mission is still moving forward.</i>

437
00:33:24,520 --> 00:33:27,560
<i>I've already faked the data</i>
<i>so those two can infiltrate.</i>

438
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:31,360
<i>I'll handle this side quickly.</i>
<i>I won't let you get killed.</i>

439
00:33:31,440 --> 00:33:32,840
Gosh.

440
00:33:33,360 --> 00:33:35,320
Is she a show-off just like her dad?

441
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:37,400
What should I do now?

442
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,520
I need to talk to the IT department.

443
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,080
- Not right now.
- It's urgent.

444
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:56,480
Nothing is more urgent
than the boss's orders.

445
00:33:58,640 --> 00:33:59,680
Leave.

446
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:12,080
Are we almost done?

447
00:34:12,159 --> 00:34:15,520
80%. About 20 more minutes
and the data should be complete.

448
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,000
Faster.

449
00:34:18,679 --> 00:34:21,000
I'm itching
to blow their heads off already.

450
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:40,080
Wait, wait, it's me!

451
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:41,639
- Sarge?
- Yeah, Sarge.

452
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:44,880
You were slow.

453
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:47,159
How did you get in?

454
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:49,199
We came as a group.

455
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:55,440
I'm not alone. Akki and Moh
are standing by as backup outside.

456
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:03,040
- Akki, pliers.
- Yeah.

457
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,160
It's tough as hell.

458
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,920
Are you nuts? I said pliers.

459
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,320
Sarge, is your side okay?

460
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:29,160
Okay in a not-okay kind of way.

461
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,160
What's with you?

462
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,520
<i>Because the time until we are slaughtered</i>

463
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,480
is getting closer and closer.

464
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:40,680
And the big-mouthed team leader
who bragged she'd take care of everything

465
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:43,280
hasn't done a damn thing yet.

466
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:49,800
Don't just talk tough.
It's not as easy as you think.

467
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,400
I never said it was easy.

468
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:55,760
But your method, you overthink everything.

469
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:59,520
Too nitpicky, too fussy.
This soft approach won't work.

470
00:35:59,600 --> 00:36:00,800
How about this?

471
00:36:02,680 --> 00:36:04,480
If I help you solve this problem,

472
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:05,760
you owe me one date.

473
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:10,160
Not funny. This is a mission,
not personal matter.

474
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:13,480
Tick-tock. Tick-tock. Tick-tock.

475
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:15,840
Tick-tock. Time keeps moving, you know.

476
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:19,880
Either I help and you go on one date
with me, or we all die.

477
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,680
No answer?

478
00:36:24,120 --> 00:36:26,840
When a woman doesn't answer,
that means yes.

479
00:36:26,920 --> 00:36:28,640
Akki, hit it big time.

480
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:32,320
Okay, Sarge. Give me a sec.

481
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,240
Almost done.

482
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,320
For our first date,

483
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:48,280
I'll give you the honor of paying.
You outrank me, after all.

484
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,960
You've got to take care
of your subordinates.

485
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,680
I want to try <i>omakase</i>.

486
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:54,360
All I've got is bullets. Want some?

487
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:56,800
<i>Okay, Sarge.</i>

488
00:36:57,560 --> 00:36:59,680
Three. Two. One.

489
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:04,800
Hey. What the hell are you doing?

490
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:11,440
Damn it, what the hell is wrong?
It was almost done, wasn't it?

491
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:14,080
I don't know.
The power went out in the whole building.

492
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,400
What about the backup system?

493
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:20,480
There is one,
but it can't be used for this task.

494
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:24,600
It's not secure for the data.
We can only use it in the server room.

495
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,600
You want to know what happened?

496
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:39,200
<i>I hacked the main power supply</i>
<i>from the central grid into the building.</i>

497
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:41,400
To avoid suspicion that it's a hack,

498
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,360
the system will reboot itself
in five minutes.

499
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:45,960
So that means we have

500
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:47,960
five minutes from now.

501
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,480
- Hey, then…
- Oh! Whoa!

502
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:50,840
Then go, now.

503
00:37:51,840 --> 00:37:52,720
Yes.

504
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,960
Something feels off.

505
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,760
- Go to the server room. Go.
- Yes, sir.

506
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:24,320
Hurry up. Finish it already.

507
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,560
It's almost done.

508
00:38:31,240 --> 00:38:32,120
Done.

509
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:48,040
Where is the agent data?

510
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:51,120
Hey, earlier the program still detected
seven people.

511
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:52,400
Where did they go?

512
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:58,320
Don't mess with me.
So do they exist or not?

513
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:03,080
They do, but I don't know where they went.

514
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:38,400
<i>If Tiangmon's right-hand man is suspicious</i>
<i>of you, I don't think it'll be long.</i>

515
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:40,360
<i>If the evidence isn't solid enough,</i>

516
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:42,960
<i>Jack won't risk making Tiangmon upset.</i>

517
00:39:43,040 --> 00:39:46,360
<i>Is this the special guest</i>
<i>you mentioned, Napa?</i>

518
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:50,160
I heard this place
offers special services.

519
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:52,560
<i>Orders have been issued</i>
<i>to increase security,</i>

520
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:55,320
especially for Natee's auction today.

521
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,840
Besides Jack,
are there any other dangerous people?

522
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:04,320
Yes, Boss.

523
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:22,160
When this happens, you get dizzy.

524
00:40:22,240 --> 00:40:24,160
One, two, three.

525
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,280
- Stop.
- Damn it. That's a big gun.

526
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,200
Shit.

527
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:35,560
When all the agents were killed, right?

528
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:36,640
Yes, Sarge.

529
00:40:37,520 --> 00:40:38,960
That's why I call them scraps.

530
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:48,520
Hey, hey.

531
00:40:50,920 --> 00:40:53,360
You bitch!
Even if you're a woman, I won't spare you.

532
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:08,160
You mole!

533
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:17,840
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
